:::::'''Old Garmentmaker:''' Thank you for your dedicated work, my esteemed guest. The symphony of weaver chirps reminds me of a special prophecy.
:::::'''Old Garmentmaker:''' "At the climax of the symphony." Hmm... The fairies of Aedes Elysiae have a passion for music, excel at playing harps, and use their melodies to create a festive atmosphere.
:::::'''Old Garmentmaker:''' Go search for the fairy harp. You should find something in the depths of the Membrance Maze.
:::::'''Old Garmentmaker:''' The prophecy mentions a "wind chime" and melody too. Perhaps it's related to this nymph carrying a wind chime.
:::;(If {{cx}}{{subst:void|<!--{"$type":"RPG.GameCore.ByCompareQuestProgress","QuestID":{"IsDynamic":false,"FixedValue":{"Value":4044401}},"Progress":{"IsDynamic":false,"FixedValue":{"Value":1}},"Inverse":true}-->}})
:::::'''Old Garmentmaker:''' Congratulations, my esteemed guest. You've ventured to the frontier of time and completed the prophesied trials.
:::::'''Old Garmentmaker:''' Prophecies are simply forgotten chronicles that, once fulfilled by one's own actions, become embedded in memory.
